(4589, 'Purple-Dyed Textiles From Wadi Murabba\'at; Historical, Archaeological and Chemical Aspects', 'Archaeological Textiles Review, 55 (2013), pp. 46 – 54', 'English', 'http://tekhelet.com/pdf/Sukenik-Purple.pdf', 'Article', 'This article presents three prestigious textiles dyed with murex shellfish, which were found in the Murabaa\'at Caves in the Judean Desert	and are dated to the Roman Period. The textiles were analyzed using High Performance Liquid Chromotography (HPLC). The results of the analysis indicate that one textile was dyed using Hexaplex Trunculus and its color tends to blu-greenish; apparently, the dye solution was exposed to the sun during the dyeing process.					', 'Royal Purple, Trunculus, Murex, HPLC', '2014-01-01', '6197352\n', 1, 1, 1, NULL, NULL),
