(13, 'And They Shall Make for Themselves Fringes on the Corners Of their Garments (Num. 15:38): The Yemenite Tallit', 'Bar-Ilan University', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Daf Parashat Hashavua.pdf', 'Article', 'In our day, the use of the tallit (prayer-shawl) is largely confined to times of prayer. To \"beautify the mitzva,\" that is, to carry out the commandment in the best possible way, some people have quotations from the Bible or blessings embroidered upon their tallit, and (as with all articles devoted to religious uses) it is always handled with respect.', ' ', ' ', '200 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(15, 'The Biblical Dye Tekhelet and its Use in Jewish Textiles', 'N/A', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/DHA21 Avignon. The Biblical Dye Tekhelet and its Use in Jewish Textiles. Reprint.pdf', 'Article', 'The Biblical Dye Tekhelet and its Use in Jewish Textiles', ' ', '2008', '509 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(16, 'Vatting Purple Dyes', 'DHA23 Montpellier', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/DHA23 Montpellier 2004 Vatting Purple Dyes.pdf', 'Presentation', ' ', ' ', '2004', '262 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(17, 'ENIGMA OF THE SEPTUAGENARIAN MUREX', 'DHA28 Poznan, Poland', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/DHA28 Poznan ENIGMA OF THE SEPTUAGENARIAN MUREX.pdf', 'Presentation', ' ', ' ', '10/22/2019', '495 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(18, 'Thermochromic behaviour of 6-bromoindigotin: key to understanding purple dyeing with banded dye-murex', 'Tekhelet Foundation', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/DOD 38 Ziderman v2.pdf', 'Article', 'In contrast to the purple dyes from all other species of shellfish, banded dye-murex (Hexaplex trunculus) typically yields a bluish tint, and is therefore identified as the hyacinthine purple of antiquity, biblical tekhelet. Chemical reactions of indoxyl and bromoindoxyl dye precursors from the hypobranchial glands compete to form a mixture of 6,6ʹ-dibromoindigotin (DBI), 6-bromoindigotin (MBI) and indigotin. A reddish purple, which was obtained from banded dye-murex by some workers, has been found to read- ily change colour to blue on heating, a phenomenon attributed to a hypothetical tinctorial lability of MBI supposedly present in the dye. Wool dyed violet with synthetic MBI indeed turns blue on mild heating. Visible absorption spectroscopy shows a bathochromic shift after heating. Gas mass spectrometry (MS), single ion monitoring (SIM) and X-ray fluorescence (XRF) spectroscopy reveal no change in chemical composition, showing that no indigotin is formed by debromination of MBI. Pure MBI also undergoes this irreversible change in colour from violet to blue at 60 °C. This discontinuous thermochromic transi- tion of MBI is the key to understanding the nature of hyacinthine purple and to explaining conflicting findings regarding the colour of the dye from banded dye-murex.', ' ', '04/27/2017', '896 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(19, 'The rate of light induced fading of indigo- dyed textiles; Biochemistry of dyes from banded dye- murex (Hexaplex trunculus)', 'Dyes in History and Archaeology meetings', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/DOD 43 Abstracts v3.pdf', 'Article', 'The following papers were presented at Dyes in History and Archaeology meetings but were sub- sequently published elsewhere or the author has chosen not to submit the work for publication.', ' ', '07/24/2017', '7.5 MB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(20, 'John Edmonds Imperial Purple Color', 'N/A', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/EdmondsColor.pdf', 'Article', ' ', ' ', 'N/A', '1.1 MB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(21, 'The Mystery of the Imperial Purple Dye', 'Imperial Purple', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/EdmondsTyrian.pdf', 'Book', 'The purpose of writing this book is to attempt to cast new light on a very ancient technology.', ' ', '2000', '7.6 MB', 1, 5, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(22, '\nGold and Jewels Found on Minoan Island Devoted to the Color Purple', 'LIVE SCIENCE', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Gold and Jewels Found on Minoan Island Devoted to the Color Purple _ Live Science.pdf', 'Article', '\nA storehouse of ancient treasures, including precious jewels and gold beads, has been uncovered by archaeologists on an island near Crete devoted to making a precious purple dye from sea snails thousands of years ago.', ' ', '12/11/2019', '986 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(23, '\"כיצד נתגלתה זיהות התכלת, פאר צבעי העולם העתיק\"', 'Keren HaTekhelet', 'Hebrew', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/History of Science 2005.pdf', 'Article', 'צבע התכלת היה פאר האוצרות של התרבויות הקדומות באגן הים התיכון. בשונה מהזהב, למשל, מוצרי תכלת היו אוצר מובהק ואפייני של האזור שלנו בעידן המקרא והתלמוד. אך, עם הכיבוש המוסלמי של א\"י, התעשייה נפסקה; מאפייניה החומריים והטכניים נשכחו ועברו לעולם האגדה והבדיון במשך 1200 שנה.', ' ', '10/23/2004', '36 KN', 2, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(24, 'Identification of indirubin and monobromoindirubins in Murex brandaris', 'Elsevier', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Identification-of-indirubin-and-monobromoindirubins-in-Murex-brandaris_2014_Dyes-and-Pigments.pdf', 'Article', 'For the first time, indirubin, 6-bromoindirubin and 60-bromoindirubin are detected in hypobranchial glands, removed from Murex brandaris molluscs. Liquid chromatography coupled to a diode array de- tector is used to analyse dimethyl sulfoxide extracts of brandaris molluscs, which were collected from the coastline of Thera island, Greece. The three aforementioned compounds are detected in small amounts compared to 6,60-dibromoindigotin and 6,60-dibromoindirubin, which correspond to very high chro- matographic peaks. Finally, small amounts of indigotin and 6-bromoindigotin are detected in the molluscan extracts.', ' ', '1/6/2014', '409 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34');
