(33, 'קונטרס המכתבים', 'המרכז למצות תכלת', 'Hebrew', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Kuntres_Michtavim_5780.pdf', 'Article', 'Listing of many Rabbonim and their thoughts on Tekhelet', 'Kuntres, Kuntreis, Hamichtavim, Rabbis, Rabbonim', '2021-01-01', '6.9 KB', 2, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2021-01-01 09:00:18'),
(34, 'TRADITIONAL STRUGGLES: STUDYING, DECIDING, AND PERFORMING THE LAW AT THE RABBI ISAAC ELCHANAN THEOLOGICAL SEMINARY', 'David J. Landes', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Landes dissertation.pdf', 'Article', 'As an open-ended process of preservation and transformation that masquerades as the transmission of an accurately maintained set of cultural prescriptions from the past, tradition entails an ongoing struggle over authenticity. In this dissertation, I examine three sites of the struggle over traditional authenticity at the Rabbi Isaac Elchanan Theological Seminary (RIETS), an all-male rabbinical seminary (yeshiva) affiliated with Yeshiva University, the flagship higher educational institution of American Modern Orthodox Judaism located in New York City. Chapter One discusses conflicts and issues pertaining to the method of study of Talmud at RIETS, addressing the following subjects: the formation of the subjectivity of the yeshiva student, competing methods of study, the relationship between methods of study and the disciplining of students, and the challenge to traditional methods of study presented by critical-historical approaches developed in the academy. The subject of Chapter Two is a highly-charged controversy among leading RIETS faculty members regarding the acceptability of the brain-death criterion of death, which is assessed from the vantage point of how the integrity and authority of the tradition is maintained in the context of an ever-present and inescapable process of cultural hybridization. Chapter Three examines the complex manner in which the performance of the commandment of tzitzit constitutes, conveys, and contests social and cultural meanings and relationships at the same time as those performing the commandment seek to discern and realize God’s expectations regarding the proper fulfillment of the commandment, the conduct of Jews within non-Jewish society, and the destiny of the Jewish people. Some of the factors complicating the determination of traditional authenticity at RIETS discussed in this dissertation include modernity, identity, politics, hybridity, ideology, materiality, and desire. In the Conclusion, I briefly discuss my status as a native anthropologist, and probe the slippery border between being a native anthropologist and anthropologically native.', ' ', 'January 2010', '2.5 MB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(35, 'Singular thermochromic effects in dyeings with indigo, 6-bromoindigo, and 6,60-dibromoindigo', 'Elsevier', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Lavinda, O.ag_Singular-thermochromic-effects-in-dyeings-with-indigo-6bromoindigo-and-66dibromoindigoArticle_2013.pdf', 'Article', 'Fundamental dyeing properties of three dyes of historical importance e indigo, 6-bromoindigo, and 6,60- dibromoindigo e on 13 fabrics are examined. The hues of the dyed fabrics vary from blue-green to blue for indigo, blue to violet for 6-bromoindigo, and violeteblue to purple for 6,60-dibromoindigo, as determined by reflectance measurements. Many of the dyed fabrics change color markedly with appli- cation of gentle heat. For indigo and 6-bromoindigo, the color changes are predominantly towards absorption of longer wavelengths (giving a bluer fabric color), while for 6,60-dibromoindigo, the color changes are towards absorption of shorter wavelengths (giving a redder fabric color). The greatest thermochromic effects are seen for dyed wool: with 6-bromoindigo, the color changes from violet to blue, while with 6,60-dibromoindigo, the color changes from violet to redepurple upon brief boiling in water. Transmission electron microscopy analysis of 6-bromoindigo-dyed carbon nanotubes, used as surrogates for dyed fabric fibers, suggests that the basis of the thermochromic effect is a change in the size distribution of dye aggregates.', ' ', '07/16/2012', '2 MB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(36, 'A Collection of Recipes for Dyeing', 'Verlqg Butzon and Bercker Kevelaer', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Leichty_Recipes_for_Dyeing_Fs_Jones_AOAT_203_1979.pdf', 'Article', ' ', ' ', '1979', '1.2 MB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(37, 'כשרות צמר כבש המרינו – בירור מחודש', 'הלכה ואקטואליה', 'Hebrew', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/MerinoWool-Ariel.pdf', 'Article', 'התורה מפרטת את חלקי הכבש העולים למזבח בקרבן השלמים, וביניהם: \"חלבו האליה תמימה\" (ויקרא ג, ט), זאת בניגוד לקרבן הבא מן הבקר ומן העז שלא הוזכרה בהם הקרבה של אליה. האליה היא זנב הכבש שיש בו הצטברות של רקמת שומן2, הנחשבת למאכל טעים במיוחד (פסחים ג, ב). הצטברות שומנית זו קיימת רק אצל כבשים, ולא בזנב הבקר והעיזים. גם בגמרא נאמר שהכבש נבדל מן העז בכך שיש\nלו אליה (שבת עז, ב; סוטה לב, ב; מנחות ג, א).', ' ', '2019', '747 KB', 2, 1, 1, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2020-02-05 21:45:34'),
(38, 'Eternal Blue', 'Mishpacha Magazine', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/MishpachaPesach2017.pdf', 'Article', 'Here I was, digging in the sand along the Mexican shores of Huatulco overlooking the endless ocean. This was no vacation, though. I was on a mission to search out a particular snail', ' ', 'April 2017', '8.6 MB', 1, 1, 0, '2020-02-05 21:45:34', '2021-02-17 05:11:10'),
