(4837, 'Murex-Purple Dye: The Archaeology behind the Production and an Overview of Sites in the Northwest Maghreb Region.', '', 'English', 'https://thelibrary.tekhelet.com/./uploads/Murex-Purple_Dye_-_The_Archaeology_behind_the_Production.pdf', 'Article', 'Looking at the archaeological indicators for purple dye production is a complex topic; there are many variables, and more often than not the evidence that remains can be attributed to other industries, unless directly linked to murex dye. Due to this, it is important to fully understand the biological, chemical and anthropological factors that may have affected the location and set up of a production site. Therefore, by walking through each stage of the production process this study aims to provide a comprehensive account of what indicators can be looked at for identifying a purple dye site, since such an account has not yet been created. The study then turns this discussion upon the several sites along the northwest Maghreb coastline which have been connected with purple dye production in order to re-evaluate the evidence provided. An overview of the information available for each site is stated and then discussed, if possible, on its probability of indicating purple dye production.', 'murex, dye', '2017-09-15', '8.5 KB', 1, 1, 1, '2020-06-06 22:41:47', '2020-06-06 22:41:47'),
